Pre-Game Insights: Both Australia and China are looking to record their first wins of the third round of the AFC World Cup qualifier.
Australia endured a woeful September camp and remain without a win in Group C.
China suffered back-to-back defeats last month in this section.
Australia's head coach Graham Arnold resigned after a poor September camp, with Tony Popovic taking over.
Australia fared well in the most recent World Cup, advancing from their group to reach the knockout stages.
China lost back-to-back matches to Japan and Saudi Arabia during the September international break.
Australia are favorites to earn maximum points in Adelaide on Thursday night.
Others: Australia's Alessandro Circati will be sidelined for the remainder of the 2024-25 campaign due to a cruciate ligament injury.
Conor Metcalfe is also unavailable for Australia due to a groin strain.
Australia may make attacking alterations with Awer Mabil and Joshua Nisbet pushing for starts.
China may stick with a centre-back pairing of Tyias Browning and Chenjie Zhu despite conceding two goals against Saudi Arabia last month.
